# AXIS Toolbox — Cursor Rules
# Project: axis-toolbox v0.4.0
# Owner: Last Man Up Inc.
# Runtime: Node.js >= 20, TypeScript 5.7 strict, pnpm workspaces
#
# Architecture: monorepo — apps/ (api, cli, web) + packages/ (snapshots, repo-parser, context-engine, generator-core)
# Frontend: React 19 + Vite 6, vanilla CSS dark theme, NO Tailwind
# Backend: Zero-dep HTTP router (NO Express/Fastify), SQLite (better-sqlite3 WAL, NO Prisma)
# Testing: Vitest 4.1, 2910 tests, 91.5% coverage, 6 determinism tests
# Generators: 80 generators across 17 programs — all must be pure functions (same input = byte-identical output)
#
# 12 YAML governance files control development policy:
#   begin.yaml (session gate) → continuation.yaml (state ledger) → axis_all_tools.yaml (program specs)
#
# Invariants:
#   - Canonical coherence > speed
#   - One vertical at a time (monolithic saturation)
#   - Evidence required for any promotion
#   - Snapshot is single source — no duplicate parsing
#   - continuation.yaml is ground truth — read on entry, update on exit
#   - Single highest-ROI per remedial cycle
#   - Deterministic generators — pure functions only
#   - Per-program billing — each program is a separate SKU
#
# Banned: express, fastify, tailwindcss, prisma, typeorm, axios, node-fetch
# Banned: stubs returning [] when data available, generators with runtime state, parallel verticals
